026-style corporate enterprise design\" to align with GFF AI's look. I'm focusing on metrics and design enhancements.\n\n\n**Exploring Design Possibilities**\n\nI'm now diving into the UI Quality Constitution to find appropriate design elements for the analytics page. Specifically, I'm auditing `/app/portal/analytics/page.tsx` for visual elements, even though it's a private portal page. My initial focus is on aligning the design with the premium aesthetic of the public site. I'm looking for elements like animated backgrounds, interactive selectors, and custom hero visuals to enhance the overall user experience and align with GFF AI's brand.\n\n\n**Improving Visual Elements**\n\nI'm now examining the CPU load stream SVG in the analytics page. I've analyzed the path calculation, confirming the x-coordinates fit within the `viewBox`. Although the current visualization is a simple blue stroke, I'm thinking about enhancing it with a gradient fill, a subtle background grid, and interactive telemetry point hovers to align with the premium GFF AI aesthetic.\n\n\n**Visualizing Enclave Location**\n\nI'm now integrating an interactive element for \"Active Enclave Location\" based on `/api/v1/analytics/client`, aiming for a dynamic summary or mini-selector linked to the CPU load simulation. This will provide a live-updating, premium feel. I'm imagining a high-fidelity visual with agent workflows or an active enclave map. The current layout and styling of `/app/portal/analytics/page.tsx` will be reviewed to enhance its overall premium quality.\n\n\n"}}
